subject: p11879886
Findings: There are diffuse interstitial opacities which are new since the prior examination. Though likely due to interstitial pulmonary edema given evidence of prior cardiac surgery, there is no evidence of central venous engorgement, cardiomegaly or pleural effusions. An alternative possibility would be atypical infection in the appropriate clinical circumstance. No confluent consolidation is identified. There is no pneumothorax. Mediastinal and hilar contours are within normal limits and unchanged from prior. Mild cardiomegaly is stable. Post-surgical changes from prior CABG are unchanged. Median sternotomy wires appear grossly intact.
Impression: New diffuse interstitial opacities likely related to pulmonary edema, though atypical infection should also be considered.
